18/12/2006
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Police detained seven people in an anti-terror operation in Istanbul at the weekend, according to local media reports Monday (December 18th). The seven are suspected of belonging to a religious terrorist organisation and involved in the murder of three people and the wounding of three others in Diyarbakir. Officials say police seized forged identity documents and CDs containing propaganda material. (Anadolu Agency, Focus - 18/12/06)
